<node id="&quot;PHYSICIAN-ASSISTED SUICIDE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Physician-Assisted Suicide is a practice where physicians provide lethal medication to terminally ill patients to end their lives, which failed in the 2012 Massachusetts general election by a narrow margin."&lt;SEP&gt;"Physician-Assisted Suicide is the practice of a physician providing a patient with the means to end their life, which was a topic in Vacco v. Quill and cases involving Maurice Généreux."&lt;SEP&gt;"Physician-assisted suicide is a practice where a doctor provides a patient with the means to end their own life, often discussed in the context of the right to die."</data>
